The incident happened under unknown circumstances. Long delays on the carriageway are reported as one of the lanes has closed in order for emergency services to assist. The crash took place at around 4.30pm today. The lorry left the M25 carriage way anti-clockwise between J25 and J24. The location of the incident is near Potters Bar and Waltham Abbey. One of the four lanes is closed. National Highways reports a delay of 45 minutes on the approach. According to the service, there are approximately eight miles of congestion. The organisation said that more updates will follow. Pictures from motorway cameras show vehicles queuing. 